      },
      "raw": "staccato strings creeping",
      "text": "Voice 1 - Raspy:\nAyo...\nVoice 1:\nDon’t touch that hat.\nVoice 2 - Crazy Whisper:\nHeh... too late.\nBoth:\nBrooms in the boiler room.",
      "lines": 8,
      "startT": 0,
      "endT": 0,
      "bars": 1
    },
    {
      "i": 5,
      "id": "brooms-in-the-boiler-room::chorus::5",
      "kind": "chorus",
      "ordinal": null,
      "voice": {
        "gender": null,
        "group": null,
        "spoken": null,
        "descriptor": "Raspy Gang Chant"
      },
      "raw": "Chorus - Raspy Gang Chant",
      "text": "Brooms in the boiler room,\nwater starts to rise,\nlittle mouse grinning with the stars in his eyes.\nBrooms in the boiler room,\nknocking at the door,\nspell got loose and it hungry for more.\nBlack-and-white world,\nbut the money still gold,\nwhole tower shaking when the wild drums roll.\nBrooms in the boiler room,\nmoon turned blue,\none wrong spell and the whole crew doomed.",
      "lines": 12,
      "startT": 0,
      "endT": 48.64,
      "bars": 20
    },
    {
      "i": 6,
      "id": "brooms-in-the-boiler-room::verse-1::6",
      "kind": "verse",
      "ordinal": 1,
      "voice": {
        "gender": null,
        "group": null,
        "spoken": null,
        "descriptor": "Rapper 1 - Raspy, Unhinged"
      },
      "raw": "Verse 1 - Rapper 1 - Raspy, Unhinged",
      "text": "I came through small with the hat pulled low,\nstars on the brim and the gloves still glow.\nStrings go stab,\nbassoon go low,\nbroom got a bucket and it march like woah.\nTold me don’t touch,\nso I touched that quick,\nnow the whole tower sick and the floorboards shift.\nOne broom, two brooms,\nthree more rise,\nblack ink magic in the cartoon eyes.\nTimpani boom when the stairwell crack,\noboe line howlin’ and the shadows clap back.\nMoonlight bends when the wand goes snap,\nshadow on the wall with a long-eared cap.\nI ain’t scared,\nI’m just deep in the trick,\ntoo much power for a little dude slick.\nBlack-and-white frame,\nbut the gold still gleam,\nmoney in the fog and the magic in steam.",
      "lines": 21,
      "startT": 48.64,
      "endT": 88.24,
      "bars": 16
    },
    {
      "i": 7,
      "id": "brooms-in-the-boiler-room::prechorus::7",
      "kind": "prechorus",
      "ordinal": null,
      "voice": {
        "gender": null,
        "group": null,
        "spoken": null,
        "descriptor": "Call and Response"
      },
      "raw": "Pre-Chorus - Call and Response",
      "text": "Voice 1:\nWho cast that?\nVoice 2:\nNot me.\nVoice 1:\nWho touched the hat?\nVoice 2:\nNot me.\nVoice 1:\nWho flooded the room?\nVoice 2:\nCouldn’t be me.\nBoth:\nThen why the broom got a whole army?",
      "lines": 14,
      "startT": 88.24,
      "endT": 97.92,
      "bars": 4
    },
    {
      "i": 8,
      "id": "brooms-in-the-boiler-room::chorus::8",
      "kind": "chorus",
      "ordinal": null,
      "voice": {
        "gender": null,
        "group": null,
        "spoken": null,
        "descriptor": "Raspy Gang Chant"
      },
      "raw": "Chorus - Raspy Gang Chant",
      "text": "Brooms in the boiler room,\nwater starts to rise,\nlittle mouse grinning with the stars in his eyes.\nBrooms in the boiler room,\nknocking at the door,\nspell got loose and it hungry for more.\nBlack-and-white world,\nbut the money still gold,\nwhole tower shaking when the wild drums roll.\nBrooms in the boiler room,\nmoon turned blue,\none wrong spell and the whole crew doomed.",
      "lines": 12,
      "startT": 97.92,
      "endT": 117.12,
      "bars": 8
    },
    {
      "i": 9,
      "id": "brooms-in-the-boiler-room::verse-2::9",
      "kind": "verse",
      "ordinal": 2,
      "voice": {
        "gender": null,
        "group": null,
        "spoken": null,
        "descriptor": "Rapper 2 - Raspy, Crazed"
      },
      "raw": "Verse 2 - Rapper 2 - Raspy, Crazed",
      "text": "I seen the mop grow teeth in the midnight haze,\nseen buckets pour rivers through a hundred stairways.\nWoodwinds laughing,\ntrumpets go crooked,\nwhole magic tower looking haunted and flooded.\nOld wizard gone,\nbut the hat stayed watching,\nevery little sparkle turned toxic.\nBroomstick army with the wooden-leg stomp,\ntap dance terror when the bassline thump.\nI told little homie,\n“You don’t know that spell.”\nHe said,\n“I know enough to make the whole room swell.”\nThen the strings start chasing,\nceiling got eyes,\nstars in the robe started falling from the sky.\nCauldron bubble,\nfloorboards split,\none more chant and the whole place flipped.\nMagic ain’t cute when the shadows get tall,\nespecially when the mouse got control of it all.",
      "lines": 22,
      "startT": 117.12,
      "endT": null,
      "bars": null
    },
